&lt;kirill&#64;shutemov.name&gt; wrote:<br />&gt;<br />&gt; Do we gain enough benefit from the microoptimization to justify existing<br />&gt; load_unaligned_zeropad()? The helper has rather confusing side-effects.<br /><br />It's a *big* deal in pathname handling, yes. Doing things a byte at a<br />time is very noticeably slower.<br /><br />If TDX has problems with it, then TDX needs to be fixed. And it's<br />simple enough - just make sure you have a guard page between any<br />kernel RAM mapping and whatever odd crazy page.<br /><br />There is nothing subtle about this at all. You probably would want<br />that guard page *anyway*.<br /><br />That "uaccepted memory" type needs to be just clearly fixed.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
